Mali ExtraLight Regular (Mali-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Mali' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight' = NID 1 'Mali ExtraLight'.

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.

NID 6 is 'Mali-ExtraLightItalic', Everything looks good.

Mali ExtraLight Italic (Mali-ExtraLightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Mali' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight Italic' = NID 1 'Mali ExtraLight' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Mali Light Regular (Mali-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Mali' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Mali Light'.

Mac NID 6

NID 6 is 'Mali-LightItalic', Everything looks good.

Mali Light Italic (Mali-LightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Mali' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light Italic' = NID 1 'Mali Light' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype or together with software distributed by one of the licensees of Monotype. This software is a valuable asset of Monotype. Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. You can learn more about Monotype by clicking here: www.monotype.com.

Error

Mali Italic (Mali-Italic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Mali-Italic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Mali Italic (Mali-Italic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Mali-Italic', Everything looks good.

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.

NID 6 is 'Mali-Medium', Everything looks good.

Mali Medium Regular (Mali-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Mali' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Mali Medium'.

Mali Medium Italic (Mali-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Mali' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium Italic' = NID 1 'Mali Medium' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Mali SemiBold Regular (Mali-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Mali' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'Mali SemiBold'.

Mali SemiBold Italic (Mali-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Mali' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold Italic' = NID 1 'Mali SemiBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Mali Bold (Mali-Bold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Mali-Bold', Everything looks good.

Pass
